The article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on May 24, 2019. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities to the Secretary of State and the Secretary of the Treasury in relation to the Sanctioning the Use of Civilians as Defenseless Shields Act. The memorandum also states that the delegated functions and authorities will be exercised in coordination with departments and agencies through the National Security Presidential Memorandum-4 process. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.